reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 20, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Excellent dress. Perfect LBD.
reviews.reviewText: The material is nice and thick, very high quality. It's great for those chilly nights when you still want to wear a little dress, because it definitely keeps you warm. It fits a little snug, so be warned. But, the material is almost "compression garment" like, so it really slims you down and is extremely flattering. Slim arms and waist effect, but bells out at the hips to create a really great shape. Im 5'5" and it wasn't too short, and the slit wasn't too high.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 2, 2024
reviews.reviewText: This dress is super flattering and has a decent amount of stretch to it. I would definitely size up if you have a larger chest, as that is where there is the least amount of give - it squished me down a bit in the chest and I am only like a 34c. It has great compression through the waist and arms and I like the slight flare in the skirt. It is a little shorter than I expected and I had to pull it down a few times, but still appropriate to wear.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 13, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Love it but can’t wear a normal bra
reviews.reviewText: I recently purchased the QINSEN Women's Sweetheart Neckline Long Sleeve Dress Side Slit Stretch Flare Mini Dress, and overall, I am quite pleased with the quality and design of the dress. The material is excellent, and it feels comfortable and stretchy, allowing for easy movement.The sweetheart neckline adds a feminine and flattering touch to the dress, and the long sleeves make it suitable for cooler weather. The side slit adds a bit of flair and adds a playful element to the overall design.However, I have decided to return the dress for a specific reason. After breastfeeding, I feel more comfortable wearing a padded bra for added support. Unfortunately, the neckline of this dress is not compatible with the bras I currently own. The bra straps would show, which is not the look I was going for.While this is a personal preference and may not be an issue for everyone, I wanted to mention it in my review. The dress itself is lovely, and if you don't mind showing your bra straps or have a different type of bra that works with the neckline, it could be a great addition to your wardrobe.I would still give this dress a four-star rating because the material and overall design are excellent. It's just unfortunate that it didn't work out for me personally due to my specific bra requirements.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 16, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 3.0 out of 5 stars Good material but not made for girls with big boobs
reviews.reviewText: I was so excited for this dress but it didnt fit. It hugged my stomach are perfectly but squished my boobs lol. Its a cute dress tho!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 24, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Cute and nice feminine fit
reviews.reviewText: This is such a cute dress but I’m just going a different direction with what I wear now. It is short, I’m 5’8 185 lbs 33-34 in waist and 43-44 in hips. New mommy and the sag after breast feeding but a good supportive bra would fix that. I don’t suspect it would have shrunk after a wash but I did not wash it, I returned it.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 7, 2023
reviews.reviewText: Short but not too short. I got black and it's flattering. I personally thought it was a tad snug for a large, but not enough to be an issue. Slight unpleasant smell, will wash first. Material is thick & not see through. Construction and quality pretty good for the price. Happy I bought.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 8, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 2.0 out of 5 stars Light blue may not be the color
reviews.reviewText: I loved the light blue color. It's beautiful HOWEVER it shows EVERYTHING! Undergarments lining shows. I think this dress would be great in different colors. The material is compressed but not so much on lower stomach area

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 30, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Cute but possibly too short for tall girls
reviews.reviewText: It’s a very flattering dress. The material is thick and buttery smooth, but I ’m 5’9 and I had to be VERY careful about bending over/sitting due to how short it is because it BARELY covered my but. The pictures make it look a bit longer than it really is. So be aware of that before ordering. Other than that it’s super cute.

El vestido es bonito y favorecedor solo que no me fije que la tela era nylon lo cual para el clima en el que vivo es muy apretado y caluroso. Siempre soy talla M pero me hubiera gustado pedir la Large solo para estar más cómoda.
